# Data Collection: Bees were collected during the 2014 field season at 13 different sites in Northern Vermont (for coords see Nosema GIS) Ran vegitation and bee abundance transects
column2: caught bombus and HB were possible. Collected flowering plants and ID'd host plant for captured bombus. Bees were dissected in 2015/2016. Ventriculi were homgenized in GITC buffer (ready for RT-qPCR work in future) and spore counts were done with a hemocytometer (2 counts 1 mean). Percent sucrose in crop was measured where possible (refractometer).
